<item>
            <title>[JDK-8325620] HTMLReader uses ConvertAction instead of specified CharacterAction for &lt;b&gt;, &lt;i&gt;, &lt;u&gt;</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8325620</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>HTMLReader specifies which action is used for handling HTML tags.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The table in HTMLReader specifies CharacterAction is used for many character-level (inline) tags whereas the implementation uses ConvertAction. The tags affected: B, FONT, I, STRIKE, SUB, SUP, U, and S after &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8323801&quot; title=&quot;&amp;lt;s&amp;gt; tag doesn&amp;#39;t strikethrough the text&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8323801&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8323801&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-4171509&quot; title=&quot;HTMLEditorKit should support StyleConstants&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-4171509&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-4171509&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; replaced CharacterAction with ConvertAction.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
ConvertAction is not a public class, nor is it a subclass of CharacterAction.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This problem was found during code review for &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8323801&quot; title=&quot;&amp;lt;s&amp;gt; tag doesn&amp;#39;t strikethrough the text&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8323801&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8323801&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/pull/17659#discussion_r1484158996&quot;&gt;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/pull/17659#discussion_r1484158996&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
